wikipedia_page.main: George Henry Wallace (18 September 1854 – 24 November 1927) was an English cricketer. He was educated at the Clergy Orphan School and Jesus College, Cambridge, and played one first-class match for Cambridge University Cricket Club in 1876. After graduating from Cambridge, Wallace became a barrister and was appointed a King's Counsel and a Bencher.
